'''Dol Donar's yacht''' was owned by [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Dol Donar II]], which he was using as their family [[Yacht/Legends|yacht]]. It was large, fast, and well armed.

Following his son [[Nathan Donar II|Nathan's]] graduation from the [[Carida Academy/Legends|Academy of Carida]], they left [[Carida/Legends|the planet]] and boarded the liner ''[[Star of Empire]]'' for a luxurious cruise. By coincidence, Nathan saw that his classman [[Kyle Katarn]] was also there, and said that if he told him he was booked, his family would had offered him a lift.

In the following hours Katarn's affiliation with [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] [[Agent/Legends|agents]] on board the ship was discovered, and after [[Skirmish on the Star of Empire|skirmish]] they escaped on their [[Transport/Legends|transport]], the ''[[Truly Sorry]]''. However the [[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial military]] officers and the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Slyder]] came back with the damaged parts of the Rebel droid [[A-Cee]].

The Governor offered to employ his own yacht for the pursuit and he, his son, Slyder and the soldiers boarded it wearing [[Environment suit/Legends|space suits]]. He insisted on taking the droid's remains with them and a [[Technician/Legends|technician]] tried to re-activate it on board while pursuing the ''Truly Sorry''. As the smaller Rebel vessel couldn't outrun the yacht, [[Jan Ors]] turned the ''Sorry'' to a course against their pursuers and opened fire, despite its stronger [[Deflector shield/Legends|shield]].

That moment, A-Cee was successfully reactivated; but spotting Nathan's Imperial uniform, its self-destruct mechanism was triggered. Slyder, who already was feeling that the humans were too incompetent to be tolerated, started shooting around before A-Cee killed everyone, destroying the yacht. Governor Donar found his end in that havoc, next to his son.<ref name="Dark Forces: Soldier for the Empire">''[[Dark Forces: Soldier for the Empire]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Dol Donar's yacht is canonical as it appears in ''[[Dark Forces: Soldier for the Empire]]''. However, it has not yet been named.

